      <title>Bug</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/oplightbox2/forum/general/bug</link>
      <description>In your ini file ImageDatatypeZoom can get the following values: 'true' or 'false'&#13;
&#13;
in you ezimage.tpl you do:&#13;
lightbox=ezini('OPLightBoxSettings', 'ImageDatatypeZoom', 'oplightbox2.ini')&#13;
&#13;
Then you do {if $lightbox} at multiple locations. The issue is it will always return true because $lightbox is a string not a boolean.</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Quoc-Huy NGUYEN DINH)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/oplightbox2/forum/general/bug</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 25 Jun 2011 12:04:57 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Great extension</title>
      <link>http://projects.ez.no/oplightbox2/forum/general/great_extension</link>
      <description>Hi Olivier&#13;
&#13;
This extension works well.&#13;
A little suggestion&#13;
&#13;
In your template for the datatype ezimage, you are using rel="XXXXX"&#13;
When XXXXX is 'lightbox', if you add '[oplightbox]' so that the image tag looks like this:&#13;
&lt;img src="..." rel="lightbox[oplightbox]" /&gt;&#13;
This will enable the 'previous' and 'next' button on the large image and also will include thumbnails of the rest of the images of the gallery, see it here:&#13;
http://www.dudleywilliams.com/Landscape/Hebrides-Collection&#13;
&#13;
Huy</description>
      <author>community@ez.no (Quoc-Huy NGUYEN DINH)</author>
      <guid>http://projects.ez.no/oplightbox2/forum/general/great_extension</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 14 Jun 2011 21:57:26 +0000</pubDate>
    </item>
